sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J133003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: aadA gene with lacIQ promoter and RBS and oriT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BBa_K125530 with an oriT postfixed, intermediate from the 2008 iGEM Hawaii team collection
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Norman Wang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K125530
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: aadA gene with lacIQ promoter and RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The ''aadA'' gene confers resistance to Spectinomycin and Streptomycin. The [[Part:BBa_I14032|lacIQ promoter]] and an [[Part:BBa_B0034|RBS] were added. This part is functional without a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Margaret Ruzicka
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was amplified from pRL1383a, an RSF1010 derived plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part will be tested on varying concentrations of antibiotics.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: P(Lac) IQ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vikram Vijayan, Allen Hsu, Lawrence Fomundam

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OriT-RP4
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: OriT-RP4 (Origin of transfer for the RP4 plasmid)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Relaxation region of self-transmissible plasmid RP4. When this part is added to a plasmid, it is transferred by RP4 through conjugation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Margaret Ruzicka
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is similar to [[Part:BBa_J01003|J01003]], which has no experience and is much longer. In the process of designing and testing this part, it will be compared to J01003.
